		<td><b>Re: Modern Mallard - Light gun and Duck Hunt mod for modern </b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />About two years ago, Hackaday carried a story about a <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=9&amp;t=14760" class="postlink">more robust prototype</a> that determines where a Wii Remote is pointed and sends that to an MCU to crop the composite output to send to a LED aimed at a Zapper's photodiode. Once the Wii Remote patent expires around 2026, it'll become practical to commercialize this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
